# Next.js 16

This project uses Next.js 16 (App Router, Turbopack, React 19).

## Async request APIs

Always `await` dynamic APIs in Server Components and Server Actions:

```ts
const cookieStore = await cookies();
const headerList = await headers();
const { id } = await params;
const sp = await searchParams;
```

## Network boundary

- Use `proxy.ts` (not `middleware.ts`) for auth redirects and request interception.
- Export `proxy` as the handler; keep `config.matcher` as needed.

## Caching

- Dynamic by default; opt into caching with `"use cache"` / `cacheComponents` when appropriate.
- `revalidateTag(tag, 'max')` for stale-while-revalidate invalidation.
- `updateTag(tag)` in Server Actions for read-your-writes after mutations.
- `refresh()` to re-fetch uncached dynamic UI without touching tagged cache.

## Components

- Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when needed (hooks, events, browser APIs).
- Colocate Server Actions in `app/actions/`.
- Wrap client-only subtrees in `Suspense` with a meaningful fallback or `null`.

## Config (already in use)

- `reactCompiler: true` in `next.config.ts`.
- Run `next dev` / `next build` with Turbopack (default); use `--webpack` only if required.

## Avoid

- Sync `params` / `searchParams` / `cookies()` / `headers()` access.
- `middleware.ts` for new request logic (deprecated in favor of `proxy.ts`).
- Single-argument `revalidateTag(tag)` (deprecated).
